text: Area code 334 is an area code for Alabama. It was created on January 15, 1995 as a split from area code 205. It was the first area code to not have the middle digit as 0 or 1. It was created on the same day as area code 360, which is in Washington. It consists of counties such as Montgomery (its capital and its county), Auburn-Opelika, and Dothan metropolitan areas. 334 Category:Alabama
title: Area code 334
